The Marzocco, a Symbol of Florence|https://www.florenceinferno.com/marzocco-symbol-of-florence/|of lions have been seen around Florence since the Middle Ages, and today you can spot them just about anywhere.  ...    The heraldic lion—also known as the Marzocco lion—is the animal symbol representing the free Republic of Florence. As  ...    The most famous Marzocco can be found in Piazza della Signoria. Sculpted by Donatello in the early 15th century from the fine-grained gray sandstone of Tuscany called pietra serena, this Marzocco lion protects the red lily, the symbol of the city. Donatello’s Marzocco was commissioned by the Republic of Florence for the apartment of Pope  ...    The strange name probably comes from the word Marte (Mars), whose Roman statue—noted by Dante and carried away by the flooding of the Arno in 1333—had previously served as Florence’s emblem. The lion is seated and  ...    Picture: [The original La marzocco
