The Florentine Catasto of 1427 - dataLegend - Druid|https://druid.datalegend.net/dataLegend/-/stories/catasto|Catasto is a tax assessment of the inhabitants of Florence and its surrounding territories between 1427 and 1429. In the Catasto, officials listed the wealth, debts, and assets of households in the Republic of Florence. Unlike many  ...    The Catasto has often been used by historians to examine the level of inequality in premodern societies. We can  ...    Also households living in villages and towns outside the city of Florence were assessed, since they were obliged to pay  ...    It seems that the high average wealth of Florentine households was caused by the presence of a group of affluent people  ...    go to Dataset Try this query yourself Within the Republic, the share of extremely poor people - those with no assets to report at all - was actually comparable between the cities and villages and the countryside: go to Dataset Try this query yourself The Catasto also reports the age of individuals in each household. Ages are interesting because they inform historians  ...   
